parameters: Veteran Mercenary: "Hey, it's time to switch."

New Mercenary: "Finally, it's time to switch. Just standing
here makes me so tired."
Veteran Mercenary: "Again, they're at it, huh..."

New Mercenary: "This one is Lord Gugukas's favorite, after
all. It's really too much."

Veteran Mercenary: "Hey, watch your mouth here. We're not
supposed to get involved, just stand guard and that's it."
New Mercenary: "Right, I forgot. Well, I'm going off then."

Veteran Mercenary: (Just stand guard without getting
involved, huh...)

Veteran Mercenary: (Even if it's for the money, doing this
kind of job... what am I really doing here?)

Complicit in evil deeds, yet merely an observer; the man
stands by the door today as well, disappointed in himself.

The man shifts his gaze to a small barred window next to the
door of the room where their employer, Gugukas, is located
and peeks inside.
